  "conclusion": "The derived c9 boundary is not a linear-projection problem: grouped-compact MoE stays red under rowchunk2 with auto selected-c1, native batch, batch-GEMV, and native-output projection controls. Switching MoE to selected_c1 makes c9 rowchunk2 generated-token equality green at [137]*9, with both auto selected-c1 linear projections and native batch linear projections. Full-native/no-rowchunk remains red even with selected_c1 MoE, and rowchunk1 selected_c1 MoE is still tail-red, so c9 needs both rowchunk2 full-attention segmentation and selected_c1 MoE. This is correctness-only diagnostic evidence; no default extension or throughput claim is made.",
